<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>/</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence submitted by </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">As</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">sociation of Convenience Stores</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ACS welcomes the opportunity to respond to the Committee’s inquiry. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ACS is a trade association, which represents over 33,500 stores across the UK, including Spar UK, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Nisa</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> Retail, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Costcutter</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">thousands of independent stores. A number of our members already charge for single-use carrier bags, both in Wales and Northern Ireland where it is already mandatory, but also in England and Scotland on a voluntary basis where the levy is yet to be introduced</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">In this response we will focus specifically on issues relating to: “the rationale for excluding particular types of retailer from the levy scheme”.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 32.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ACS supports the introduction of a carrier bag levy in England, set out along similar lines as that already in place in Wales, and planned for Scotland, however we do not support the proposed exemption for small businesses. In this submission, we make the following recommendations:</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-indent:36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Recommendations:</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">a)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Include convenience store retailers within the scope of the English carrier bag levy to encourage charitable donations.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">b)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Exempt small businesses with less than 250 FTE employees from having to report back information such as the proceeds of the charge to central Government. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Support for the levy</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 32.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The experience of retailers in Wales highlights the benefits a levy can bring, with members reporting not only in reductions in waste, but also financial savings and increases in the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> funds </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">they donate to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> national and local charities. </span></li><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Figures from our Voice of Local Shops Survey from August 2013 found that 62% of British convenience store owners support a single-use carrier bag levy, which includes Welsh retailers where the scheme is already in place, and in England and Scotland. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">In Wales, 82% of retailers cited their</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> support for a carrier bag levy. These figures are </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">a clear indicati</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">on for the success of the levy already in place in Wales, and of the future success it would have in England</span><a name="_ftnref1"></a><a href="#_ftn1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 32.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">However, in order for a similar levy to be successful in England, it is essential that it does not impose excessive or unnecessary burdens on retail, and that any changes are clearly communicated to retailers and customers before implementation. We therefore welcomed the announcement that the proposed carrier bag levy for England will broadly follow those found in Wales and the proposed scheme in Scotland.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Proposed small business exemption</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The key difference between the proposals is the planned exemption of small businesses who employ fewer than 250 staff. While ACS understands the reasoning behind this proposal, we believe that this exemption is unnecessary for the following reasons:</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">It would be difficult for retailers with stores in other parts of the UK to differentiate between the requirements for the different schemes.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The inconsistency between large and small stores would create confusion for customers, and make messaging harder to communicate.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">It could create a misleading perception that larger stores are more socially or environmentally responsible</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The support from small retailers to be included in the scheme (please refer to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">para</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> 4).</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span></li></ul></ul><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">In a recent survey of our members, a large number of retailers called specifically for small businesses to be included within the scope of the charge, with one independent retailer saying: </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">“We need to charge for plastic bags. Customers will only cut back on usage if it will cost them money</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> We would be delighted to give the money raised to charity</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> and it would not be difficult to organise</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Please lobby the Government</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> to include small shops</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">.” David </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Charman</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">, Owner, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Parkfoot</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> Garage Ltd.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="9" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">To ensure consistency with Wales and Scotland, and to ensure clear and consistent communication for customers, ACS would support the adoption of the current models in place in Wales and Scotland of including small businesses within the scope of the charge, but exempting them from the reporting requirements</span><a name="_ftnref2"></a><a href="#_ftn2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. This solution would maximise the impact of the levy while minimising regulatory burdens on retailers. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="10" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">This approach found in Wales and Scotland is preferable to exempting retailers from the charge altogether, given the support from small businesses and the opportunity the levy provides for retailers to support local charities and environmental causes without the administrative burden of reporting their proceeds to central Government. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Supporting existing retail practices</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="11" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ACS’ most recent Voice of Local Shops survey found that 76% of retailers across Britain were already collecting money for charity (with an average of 74% across the English regions) and that almost a quarter (22%) of British retailers are already charging for carrier bags (with an average of 16% in the English regions and Scotland where a mandatory charge has not yet been introduced). This large number of shops which are already donating money to charities and those stores already having introduced a carrier bag charge without a mandatory levy would suggest a levy would complement existing business practices. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="12" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The survey also shows that shops in Wales are most likely to raise money for charity, with 90% stating that they give money to good causes. Arguably, there is a strong correlation between this high percentage and the introduction of the carrier bag levy in 2011. It would also imply that the number of shops engaging with local and national charities will increase at a significant level if it is mandatory for them to charge for single-use carrier bags in England and Scotland too.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="13" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">These figures highlight the benefits of the levy being applied to all retailers. However, as stated above, it is essential that the regulations do not impose unnecessary burdens on retail. We therefore strongly believe that small businesses should be exempt from reporting their proceeds centrally. This exemption would strike a balance between encouraging retailers to donate the proceeds of the charge to good causes without the burdens associated with reporting back to Government. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><a name="_GoBack"></a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">9 December 2013</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><br style="clear:both; mso-break-type:section-break; page-break-before:always" /><div><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Annex 1 – Voice of Local Shops Survey 2013: Carrier Bag Questions</span></p><table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; float:left; margin:0pt 9pt; width:767pt"><tr style="height:12.75pt"><td colspan="3" style="padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:middle; width:673pt"><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">Thinking about the use of carrier bags by your customers, which of the following statements do you support? </span></p></td><td style="padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:bottom; width:94pt"><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p></td></tr><tr style="height:12.75pt"><td style="padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:middle; width:523.55pt"><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Base: All respondents</span></p></td><td style="padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:bottom; width:72.9pt"><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p></td><td style="padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:bottom; width:76.55pt"><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p></td><td style="padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:bottom; width:94pt"><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p></td></tr><tr style="height:12.75pt"><td style="padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:bottom; width:523.55pt"><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p></td><td style="background-color:#60497a; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:bottom; width:72.9pt"><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:center"><span style="color:#ffffff; font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">Study Total</span></p></td><td style="background-color:#60497a; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-rig